00001 /*
00002       SWFUpload.SWFObject Plugin
00003 
00004       Summary:
00005             This plugin uses SWFObject to embed SWFUpload dynamically in the page.  SWFObject provides accurate Flash Player detection and DOM Ready loading.
00006             This plugin replaces the Graceful Degradation plugin.
00007 
00008       Features:
00009             * swfupload_load_failed_hander event
00010             * swfupload_pre_load_handler event
00011             * minimum_flash_version setting (default: "9.0.28")
00012             * SWFUpload.onload event for early loading
00013 
00014       Usage:
00015             Provide handlers and settings as needed.  When using the SWFUpload.SWFObject plugin you should initialize SWFUploading
00016             in SWFUpload.onload rather than in window.onload.  When initialized this way SWFUpload can load earlier preventing the UI flicker
00017             that was seen using the Graceful Degradation plugin.
00018 
00019             <script type="text/javascript">
00020                   var swfu;
00021                   SWFUpload.onload = function () {
00022                         swfu = new SWFUpload({
00023                               minimum_flash_version: "9.0.28",
00024                               swfupload_pre_load_handler: swfuploadPreLoad,
00025                               swfupload_load_failed_handler: swfuploadLoadFailed
00026                         });
00027                   };
00028             </script>
00029             
00030       Notes:
00031             You must provide set minimum_flash_version setting to "8" if you are using SWFUpload for Flash Player 8.
00032             The swfuploadLoadFailed event is only fired if the minimum version of Flash Player is not met.  Other issues such as missing SWF files, browser bugs
00033              or corrupt Flash Player installations will not trigger this event.
00034             The swfuploadPreLoad event is fired as soon as the minimum version of Flash Player is found.  It does not wait for SWFUpload to load and can
00035              be used to prepare the SWFUploadUI and hide alternate content.
00036             swfobject's onDomReady event is cross-browser safe but will default to the window.onload event when DOMReady is not supported by the browser.
00037              Early DOM Loading is supported in major modern browsers but cannot be guaranteed for every browser ever made.
00038 */
